	<h4><u><b>General Instructions:</b></u></h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Total duration of examination is 180 minutes.</li><br>
		<li>The clock will be set at the server. The countdown timer in the top right corner of screen will display the remaining time available for you to complete the examination. When the timer reaches zero, the examination will end by itself. You will not be required to end or submit your examination.</li><br>
		<li>The Question Palette displayed on the lower side of screen</li><br>
		<li>
			Indicates you have answered the question
		</li><br>
		<li>Indicates current viewing question number</li><br>
		<li>Indicates you have not answered the question yet</li><br>
	</ul>

	<h4><u><b>Navigating to a Question:</b></u></h4>
	<ul>
		<li>To answer a question, do the following:</li><br>
			Click on the question number in the Question Palette at the lower of your screen to go to that numbered question directly. After marking answer please click on submit but for processing next question.
	</ul>
	<br>
	<h4><u><b>Answering a Question :</b></u></h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Procedure for answering a multiple choice type question:</li><br>
			<ol>
				<li>To answer a question, Click on the button against the chosen option among the given four options.</li>
				<li>To change your chosen answer, click on the button of another option</li>
				<li>There is no option to deselect your chosen answer once answering.</li>
			</ol><br>
		<li>To change your answer to a question that has already been answered, first select that question for answering.</li><br>
		<li>Note that ALL Questions for which answers are marked or submitted will be considered for evaluation.</li>
	</ul><br>

	<h4><u><b>Navigating through sections:</b></u></h4>
	<ul>
		<li>Sections in this question paper are displayed on the top bar of the screen. Questions in a section can be viewed by clicking on the section name. The section you are currently viewing is highlighted.</li><br>
		<li>After clicking the submitted button on the last question for a section, you will automatically be taken to the first question of the next section.</li><br>
		<li>You can shuffle section(subject) and questions anytime during the examination as per your convenience only during the time stipulated</li>
	</ul>
